  "text": "Children's awareness about social confl ict was also investigated in Northern Ireland, with children aged 6, 9, and 12. The authors [CITATION_1] found that most 6-year-olds were unaware of the confl ict. They attributed this to the type of \"confl ict at the level of relatively abstract groups\" (pp. 233) and to efforts by parents and teachers to shield children from the confl ict. These fi ndings suggest that confl icts may have different infl uences on children depending on the information disseminated by the respective SPIR.",
